    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-08-31T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-08-31T15:00:00-05:00" n="384"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d384">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.77/468a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in China</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MJA1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-08-31T16:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 31, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Tokyo will repeat to you a long cable dealing with the <persName
                        corresp="#p_SJF1">Stevens</persName> commission and a policy which this
                    Government proposes for the handling of the Trans-Siberian Railway system
                    including Chinese Eastern. On receipt of it you will please present the matter
                    to the Chinese Government and urge it to consent to and to abide by the policy
                    therein outlined.</p>
                <p>The policy suggested seems to this Government the only solution of a problem
                    which is very complicated and which may otherwise become most embarrassing.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
